---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "@lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Oren Sultan — Senior DevOps Engineer, platform & GitOps">
  <div class="wrap-narrow">
    <h1 style="margin-top:3rem;">About</h1>
    <p>
      I'm <strong>Oren Sultan</strong>, Senior DevOps &amp; Platform Engineer based in Israel.
      10+ years in infrastructure — starting from an intelligence unit background, through network
      engineering at Motorola, and into cloud-native platform work.
    </p>
    <p>
      I spend most of my time inside Kubernetes clusters, Pulumi/Terraform stacks, and GitOps
      pipelines — usually embedded within product R&amp;D teams. I care about the gap between
      "works in staging" and "holds up in production."
    </p>
    <p>
      Since 2021 I work at <strong>Tikal – Fullstack as a Service</strong>, moving between client
      engagements and building things that need to actually run. I also run Tikal's DevOps group
      routine — sessions, tech talks, and knowledge-sharing across the team.
    </p>
    <p>Father to Dror and Peleg.</p>

    <h2>Experience</h2>

    <h3>Sentra</h3>
    <p><em>May 2025 – Present | Senior Platform Engineer</em></p>
    <p>Data security SaaS. Sole platform engineer — own the full infrastructure stack across AWS (multi-region EKS), Azure, and GCP.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Migrated monolithic Pulumi codebase to a modular GitOps model with ArgoCD ApplicationSets and ESO for secrets sync</li>
      <li>Replaced static node groups with Karpenter; cut compute costs ~30%</li>
      <li>Deployed KEDA for event-driven scaling of data-scan workloads</li>
      <li>Introduced Twingate for zero-trust internal access, replacing VPN dependencies</li>
      <li>Led least-privilege DB access initiative — per-service scoped roles for MongoDB Atlas and RDS across 25+ services</li>
      <li>Observability stack: Datadog APM + Coralogix log aggregation</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Tikal – Fullstack as a Service</h3>
    <p><em>Aug 2021 – Apr 2025 | DevOps Engineer</em></p>
    <p>Consulting across multiple product R&amp;D teams, plus running the internal DevOps practice:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>LinearB</strong> (Mar–Apr 2026) – K8s/OpenShift hardening, GitOps, TLS/PKI, Helm, Terraform</li>
      <li><strong>TerraSecurity</strong> (Aug 2025–Feb 2026) – AI pentesting platform; replaced monolithic Pulumi with ArgoCD GitOps, EKS Operators, Langfuse, Coralogix</li>
      <li><strong>ZoomInfo</strong> (Aug 2024–Sep 2025) – Release automation via GitHub Actions and ArgoCD; refactored Node.js automation system; OneBranch repo solution; GCP/BigQuery</li>
      <li><strong>Beti Tech</strong> (Aug 2023–Sep 2024) – EKS, ArgoCD, Terraform/Terragrunt, Crossplane, Karpenter</li>
      <li><strong>Capitolis</strong> (Dec 2022–Jan 2023) – Helm umbrella charts, ArgoCD ApplicationSets, EKS, Terraform</li>
      <li><strong>GigaSpaces</strong> (Oct 2021–Jun 2022) – AWS EKS, Jenkins-as-Code, Nexus, ArgoCD</li>
      <li><strong>DevOps Group Lead</strong> (2025–2026) – Ran the internal DevOps circle: sessions, tech talks, Tech Radar curation</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Motorola Solutions</h3>
    <p><em>Dec 2017 – Aug 2021 | Integration Engineer</em></p>
    <p>Global WiFi NOC at Airport City. Network monitoring (SolarWinds, LibreNMS), Python automation, TCP/IP troubleshooting across enterprise WAN/WLAN deployments.</p>

    <h2>Projects</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Least-Privilege DB Access</strong> – Replaced shared atlasAdmin/master credentials with per-service scoped roles for MongoDB Atlas and RDS across 25+ microservices; Atlas custom roles + ESO + K8s Secrets.</li>
      <li><strong>Enterprise Cloud Native Platform</strong> – Multi-cloud (AWS/GCP/Azure) platform with ArgoCD ApplicationSets and Crossplane for self-service infrastructure.</li>
      <li><strong>K-agent</strong> – AI-powered GitOps agent (FastAPI, LiteLLM) for automated infrastructure provisioning.</li>
      <li><strong>Dev Environment as Code</strong> – Reproducible local setup for a full engineering org; Ansible + dotfiles, covering build tools, CLIs, and IDE config.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Skills</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloud:</strong> AWS (EKS, EC2, Lambda, RDS, Secrets Manager), GCP (GKE, BigQuery), Azure (AKS)</li>
      <li><strong>IaC &amp; GitOps:</strong> Pulumi, Terraform, Terragrunt, Crossplane, ArgoCD, Helm</li>
      <li><strong>Kubernetes:</strong> EKS, GKE, AKS, Karpenter, KEDA, ESO, Helm, Operators</li>
      <li><strong>CI/CD:</strong> GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, ArgoCD ApplicationSets</li>
      <li><strong>Observability:</strong> Datadog, Coralogix</li>
      <li><strong>Security &amp; Networking:</strong> Twingate, TLS/PKI, IAM, Okta</li>
      <li><strong>AI/ML Tooling:</strong> LangFuse, LiteLLM, RAG (ChromaDB)</li>
      <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Python, Bash, Go, HCL</li>
      <li><strong>Databases:</strong> MongoDB Atlas, MySQL, RDS (PostgreSQL)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Education</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>BSc in Electrical Engineering</strong> - SCE Shamoon College of Engineering (2013-2017)</li>
      <li><strong>DevOps Experts Academy</strong> (2020)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href={SITE.social.resume} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resume</a><br/>
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.social.email}`}>{SITE.social.email}</a><br/>
      <a href={SITE.social.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a><br/>
      <a href={SITE.social.medium} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Medium</a><br/>
      <a href={SITE.social.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a><br/>
      <a href="/contact/">Contact form</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>